        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 14 at 1:11PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>A short heavy snow shower is moving northward along the divide
early this afternoon. This heavy snow shower will affect areas
around Flesher and Rogers Pass and the Lincoln area.

Visibility will fall below a quarter of a mile for a short time.
New snow accumulations of around one half inch are likely as this
snow shower moves through.

Those traveling on Highway 200 over Rogers Pass and through the
Lincoln area should be alert for quickly changing road conditions.
</description>
